title: For Sale:  NICE Beretta 9 mm
postcontent:
Maker: Beretta
Caliber: 9 mmMags:  TWO high capacity 17 round mags (17 +1)Condition:  like NEW!  A real Gem.
The PX4 is the latest and greatest design by the famous Beretta firearms maker. Using short recoil, locked-breech action, it has an innovative rotating barrel lock proven for performance on the Beretta Cougar to close up the chamber for reliable performance.
Gun is built with all the the quality and workmanship that Beretta is famous for.
ERGONOMICS AND RECOILHandles and shoots extremely well.
Slide mounted ambidextrous safety/decock.
Contours in the slide make the PX4 Storm look sexy and sleek — just what one would expect from an Italian-made Beretta. There are slide cuts both fore and aft that are neither too sharp nor too slippery, and the slide is virtually snag free for an easy draw.
Grip angle facilitates a natural point-of-aim for me, more so than the grip angle of a GLOCK, which tends toward the high side. The upper rear of the grip has a curved recess that creates a beaver tail of sorts to give a snug fit and prevent hammer bite.
Mag release can easily be switched for left-handed shooters.
INNOVATIVE AND RELIABLE LOCKING SYSTEM
Very unique barrel locking system – it uses lugs on the barrel and a peg on the locking block that fits into a channeled groove fitted on the barrel. This creates robustness and long-life: Extremely robust locking lugs, located at 180° in order to ensure the best distribution of locking forces when firing. The reduced friction areas between the barrel and the slide, as well as the central block, guarantee a remarkable fluency of operation and great reliability, even under poor climate conditions. In addition, the barrel features an enlarged external muzzle diameter that ensures a precise and constant barrel-to-slide coupling, shot after shot, considerably enhancing the accuracy of the pistol.  Furthermore, the reduction of the external barrel diameter for its remaining length guarantees an improved rear and forward travel of the slide during the operating cycle.
Additional benefits include a lower bore-axis and the channeling of recoil energy into the rotation of the barrel, which decreases muzzle flip and recoil, allowing for faster and more accurate follow up shots.
EXTREMELY SOLID build due to the rotating barrel and locking lock design – it has no rattle and almost no side-to-side play between the slide and frame rails.
Really a sweet, smooth trigger pull smooth, without any take-up and a clean break.
TRIGGER AND ACCURACY
Unlike many guns today, the PX4 is not striker fired and instead uses an exposed and traditional hammer that cocks after the first round. It’s more of a low profile, modernized hammer and provides a nice mix of an authentic gun experience and modern design.
Nice clean trigger break for shooting and great overall experience in both single and double action.
One of the most unique features is the rotating barrel, which contributes to less felt recoil.
Three dot sights: Super-LumiNova sights are rechargeable alternatives to more expensive night sights.
RELOADING AND DISASSEMBLY
Magazine well is cavernous and takes well to indexing the feed lips by feel in field conditions.
Field stripping the PX4 is rather similar to that of the Glock, using two small pegs, one on each side of the frame, as a takedown lever. When reassembling you will notice the exceptionally tight tolerances under which the gun was designed – this is where your accuracy comes from.
 *No trades. No silly low offers -- these messages will not be returned.
 This item is for sale.  It is not necessary to ask if it is still available.  If you are reading the ad, it is available.

Springfield’s Newest 9 mm XD 4.0 - MOD 2!

This is Springfield’s latest version of the XD that took the gun world by storm with new benchmarks in handling, accuracy, reliability, and safety.
Gun is built with all the quality and workmanship that Springfield is famous for.
FEATURES, ERGONIMICS, HANDLING & CONTROL
 You’ll first notice the new styling (in contrast with its predecessor’s blocky design (similar to the Glock ‘brick in your hand feel’).   An excellent job modernizing the gun’s graphics, cut angles and ergonomics. The Mod.2’s a much sexier pierce than the prior one.
The new gun is cleaner. Note the rounded the trigger guard. The indent aligned and supported the shooter’s trigger finger; the square trigger guard offered secure purchase for a shooter’s support hand’s index finger (especially when gloved). 
The Mod.2 replaces the old XD’s straight-up reat sight with a slinky, low-profile extended sight, which is snag-free and holster friendly.
It also has a slimmer slide. Note the new “posi-wedge” serrations are a lot easier to work.
A slimmer takedown lever for increased snaglessness. The “high-hand beavertail” positions the shooter’s hand better.
The Mod.2 builds on the XD’s ergonomic excellence to be even better. Perfectly balanced for rapid fire and rapid fire exercises and shot recovery.Trigger breaking point is sharp, clean and predictable. Easy for follow up shots and tremendous accuracy, especially rapid fire.  With the pistol’s high-hand grip reducing felt recoil and the XD’s natural pointing prowess, shooters can reacquire their sight picture and return to target with life-saving speed and efficiency.
